This bow is unusual in that it has a aluminum arrow rest assembly that is machined to accept the two arrow guide strips that form a slot to accept the fin adapters and arrow. I want to issue a warning to those of you that might be interested in the listing referenced in the title; This man is an arrogant, quite likely ignorant, and poor example of a responsible gun owner. The perfect storm of a person very likely incapable of being held to a verbal contract, which equates to a very risky potential business deal. Besides his inflated asking price, I present the following as evidence.

I sent him a simple message, which follows:
"Please edit or remove the picture with your finger on the trigger. Responsible gun ownership means NEVER putting your finger on the trigger until you are aimed at and ready to shoot your target. Thank you."

His reply, verbatim:
"Do you seriously have nothing better to do? A responsible gun owner.... im 40 years old with a family. Never had a problem I have my permit to carry. The guns empty. Responsible... I have 2 jobs 3 kids and a wife. I think im pretty responsible."

My reply:
"Yes, I seriously have nothing better to do than help raise awareness of irresponsible gun ownership. Your response does nothing to prove responsibility, only arrogance. Where did you get your PTC? Your instructor has 1 of 2 possible problems: 1) Failed to discuss the 4 rules of gun safety, or 2) Failed to stress the importance of gun safety. Here's a refresher from the NRA;
1) ALWAYS keep the gun pointed in a safe direction.
2) ALWAYS keep your finger off the trigger until ready to shoot.
3) ALWAYS keep the gun unloaded until ready to use.
4) ALWAYS treat every gun as if it is loaded."

I'll be more than happy to forward the exchange in it's original context with a screen shot as proof of my accusations.
